\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qc
\b\f0\fs40 Workspace Walkthrough: Hyper-V Lab Automation Suite\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1

\pard\sa100\sl276\slmult1
\b\fs32 What Is This?\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1
This workspace is a \b PowerShell-based automation toolkit\b0  for rapidly provisioning Windows Server and Windows 11 lab environments on \b Hyper-V\b0 . It can stand up entire Active Directory domains with Domain Controllers, DHCP servers, and full Remote Desktop Services (RDS) farms \endash  all from a single host machine.\par

\pard\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par

\pard\sa100\sl276\slmult1
\b\fs32 Centralized Configuration Files\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1

The suite uses two centralized configuration files that control the entire deployment ecosystem:\par

\pard\fi-360\li720\sa100\sl276\slmult1
\u8226?\tab\b\f1 sys_bootstrap.ini\f0\b0  \endash  Single-line file containing the default Administrator initialization code. Read by all scripts that need authorization strings.\par
\u8226?\tab\b\f1 switch.txt\f0\b0  \endash  Generated by \f1 switch.ps1\f0 . Stores the virtual switch name, gateway IP, network address, prefix length, subnet mask, and DHCP range. All scripts read this file for network settings.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1
Modifying either file uniformly trickles down to all scripts automatically.\par

\pard\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par

