\pard\sa100\sl276\slmult1
\b\fs32 File-by-File Summary\b0\fs22\par

\pard\sa60\sl276\slmult1
\b\fs26 Foundation Scripts\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1

\b\f1 switch.ps1\f0\b0  (175 lines)\line \b Checks if Hyper-V is installed\b0  (offers to enable if not). \b Auto-detects existing switches\b0  and extracts their configuration to safely skip creation if already configured. Supports two modes: \b default\b0  (\f1 -Default\f0  flag) and \b custom\b0  (prompts for switch name and CIDR). Creates the internal vSwitch, assigns gateway, configures NAT, and writes all settings to \f1 switch.txt\f0 .\par

\b\f1 setup.ps1\f0\b0  (350 lines)\line \b Checks if Hyper-V is installed\b0  (offers to enable if not). Downloads Server 2019/2022/2025 eval VHDs and Server 2016 / Win11 Enterprise ISOs via BITS. Creates reference VMs with dynamic RAM. Includes Gen 2 + TPM for Win11. Reads \f1 switch.txt\f0  for the switch name and \b detects if the switch exists\b0  in Hyper-V; if missing, offers to run \f1 switch.ps1\f0  automatically.\par


\b\f1 unattend.ps1\f0\b0  (150 lines)\line Injects a dynamic unattend.xml into each reference VM via PowerShell Direct, then runs sysprep /generalize /oobe /shutdown \b asynchronously on all VMs\b0 . Uses a \b 15-minute global timeout loop\b0  to wait for all VMs to simultaneously shut down, verifying success. Removes the VMs from Hyper-V and cleans up the config folders. Golden image VHDs in .\\goldenImage are preserved. initialization code pulled from \f1 sys_bootstrap.ini\f0 .\par

\pard\sa60\sl276\slmult1
\b\fs26 Core Engines\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1

\b\f1 deploy.ps1\f0\b0  (280 lines)\line The central deployment engine. Reads the virtual switch name and DHCP range from \f1 switch.txt\f0 . \b Checks DHCP availability\b0  before deploying: verifies either the host has the DHCP role with a matching scope, or a VM named "DHCP" is running. If neither is found, warns and offers to run \f1 DHCP.ps1\f0 . Copies sysprepped golden images via parallel robocopy jobs, creates VMs (Gen 1 or Gen 2), boots them, and loops hostname rename via PowerShell Direct until verified. Supports OS 2019/2022/2025/11.\par

\b\f1 createDC.ps1\f0\b0  (104 lines)\line Reads switch name and \b gateway IP from \f1 switch.txt\f0\b0 . Calls deploy.ps1 to create a VM, then assigns a static IP with the dynamic gateway, installs AD-Domain-Services, and promotes the server to a new forest/domain.\par

\b\f1 joindomain.ps1\f0\b0  (139 lines)\line Connects to the DC to discover its IP, then iterates through member VMs: sets DNS to the DC's IP and runs Add-Computer to join the domain. Verifies join in a polling loop.\par

\pard\sa60\sl276\slmult1
\b\fs26 Standalone Utilities\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1

\b\f1 DHCP.ps1\f0\b0  (155 lines)\line Reads all network settings from \f1 switch.txt\f0 . \b Detects if the host is Windows Server\b0  (via Win32_OperatingSystem.ProductType). If Server, offers to install DHCP directly on the host (scoped only to the lab network range). If declined or if host is a workstation, deploys a standalone "DHCP" VM with the role configured using the range from switch.txt.\par

\b\f1 cleanup.ps1\f0\b0  (51 lines)\line Scans .\\hyperv\\ for folders that don't match any running Hyper-V VM and deletes them. Safety guard: aborts if no VMs are found.\par

\pard\sa60\sl276\slmult1
\b\fs26 Orchestrators\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1

\b\f1 Domainsetup.ps1\f0\b0  (62 lines)\line Interactive wrapper: prompts for DC name, domain, OS, member VMs, and domain-join flag. Chains createDC.ps1 \u8594? deploy.ps1 \u8594? joindomain.ps1.\par

\b\f1 RDS.ps1\f0\b0  (193 lines)\line Full RDS farm orchestrator. Validates that all role targets exist in the VM pool, then chains DC creation \u8594? VM deployment \u8594? domain join \u8594? New-RDSessionDeployment \u8594? adds Gateway and Licensing roles.\par

\pard\sa60\sl276\slmult1
\b\fs26 Configuration & Documentation\b0\fs22\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1

\b\f1 sys_bootstrap.ini\f0\b0  \endash  Single-line authorization string file. All scripts read this as the default Administrator initialization code.\par
\b\f1 switch.txt\f0\b0  \endash  Generated by switch.ps1. Stores SwitchName, Gateway, NetworkAddress, PrefixLength, SubnetMask, DHCPStart, DHCPEnd. All scripts read this for network configuration.\par
\b\f1 Guidance.txt\f0\b0  \endash  User-facing guide: deployment sequence, parameters, and usage examples per script.\par
\b\f1 readme.txt\f0\b0  \endash  Developer wiki: internal logic, variable names, constraints, and inter-script dependencies.\par
\b\f1 sys_bootstrap.ini\f0\b0  \endash  Auto-generated by setup.ps1 on first run. Stores the master lab initialization code used by all downstream scripts.\par

\pard\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par

\pard\sa100\sl276\slmult1
\b\fs32 Key Design Patterns\b0\fs22\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa100\sl276\slmult1
\u8226?\tab\b Centralized authorization strings\b0  \endash  sys_bootstrap.ini is the single source of truth for all Administrator initialization codes\par
\u8226?\tab\b Centralized networking\b0  \endash  switch.txt is the single source of truth for switch name, gateway, subnet, and DHCP range\par
\u8226?\tab\b PowerShell Direct\b0  \endash  All guest-OS operations use Invoke-Command -VMName (no network required)\par
\u8226?\tab\b Parallel operations\b0  \endash  BITS downloads and robocopy jobs run in parallel with live progress monitoring\par
\u8226?\tab\b Polling verification\b0  \endash  Hostname renames and domain joins are verified in retry loops\par
\u8226?\tab\b Transcript logging\b0  \endash  Every script writes to .\\logs\\<ScriptName>_<timestamp>.txt\par
\u8226?\tab\b Switch detection\b0  \endash  setup.ps1 auto-detects if the virtual switch exists and offers to create it\par
\u8226?\tab\b Host OS detection\b0  \endash  DHCP.ps1 detects Windows Server and offers direct host installation\par

\pard\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw10\brsp20\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par

